rue,"entry_ids":["n36567"],"search_url":"https://lanelexicon.com/?s=%D8%AA%D9%8E%D9%83%D9%8E%D8%A8%D9%8E%D9%91%D8%B1%D9%8E"}},"translations":null,"definition":{"source":"wiktextract","senses":[{"pos":"verb","gloss":"to be arrogant","examples":[{"text":"قَالَ فَٱهْبِطْ مِنْهَا فَمَا يَكُونُ لَكَ أَنْ تَتَكَبَّرَ فِيهَا فَٱخْرُجْ إِنَّكَ مِنَ ٱلصَّاغِرِينَ"}]},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"verbal noun of تَكَبَّرَ (takabbara) (form V)","tags":["form-of","noun-from-verb"]},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"arrogance, pride, vanity, hauteur, haughtiness"}]},"etymology":{"source":"wiktextract","text":"Verbal noun of تَكَبَّرَ (takabbara)."},"ipa":["/ta.kab.ba.ra/","/ta.kab.bur/"],"lanes_definition":{"source":"lanes","entries":[{"entry_id":"n36567","headword_ar":"تكبّر","root":"kbr","body":[{"kind":"text","text":"and ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Astkbr","text_ar":"استكبر","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, K) and ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"tkAbr","text_ar":"تكابر","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"(K)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He magnified himself; behaved proudly, haughtily,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"insolently;"},{"kind":"text","text":"(K;) syn."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"taEaZ~ama","text_ar":"تَعَظَّمَ"},{"kind":"text","text":": (S:) or"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"tkb~r","text_ar":"تكبّر"},{"kind":"text","text":"signifies, as used in the Kur, vii. 143,"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"he considered himself as of the most excellent of the creation, and as having rights which others have not:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(Zj:) or this verb has two significations: one of them,"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"he did really good and great actions, exceeding the good actions of others;"},{"kind":"text","text":"and hence"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Almutakab~iru","text_ar":"المُتَكَبِّرُ"},{"kind":"text","text":"[applied to God] in the Kur, lix. 23: the other,"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"he affected to do such actions, and boasted of great qualities which he did not possess;"},{"kind":"text","text":"as do the generality of men; and hence,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"mutakab~ir","text_ar":"مُتَكَبِّر"},{"kind":"text","text":"in the Kur, xl. 37; and the verb itself in the Kur, vii. 143: and ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Astkbr","text_ar":"استكبر","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"is nearly syn. with"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"tkb~r","text_ar":"تكبّر"},{"kind":"text","text":", and likewise has two significations: one of them,"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"he endeavoured, and sought, to become great;"},{"kind":"text","text":"and to do so, when the manner and place and time are such as are requisite, is praiseworthy: the other,"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"he boasted of qualities which he did possess, and feigned such qualities;"},{"kind":"text","text":"and to do so is blameable; and in this sense the verb is used in the Kur, ii. 32: (El-Basáïr:) and ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"tkAbr","text_ar":"تكابر","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"signifies"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"he feigned himself great in estimation"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"rank"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"dignity,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"in age."},{"kind":"text","text":"(A, TA.) ―         -b2-"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"tkb~r EalaY A@ll~`hi","text_ar":"تكبّر عَلَى ا@للّٰهِ"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He magnified himself against God, by refusing to accept the truth."},{"kind":"text","text":"(El-Basáïr.) ―         -b3-  ["},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"tkb~r Eano ka*aA","text_ar":"تكبّر عَنْ كَذَا"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He was disdainful of such a thing; he disdained it; turned from it with disdain; he held himself above it;"},{"kind":"text","text":"like"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"taEaZ~ama","text_ar":"تَعَظَّمَ"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"taEaAZama","text_ar":"تَعَاظَمَ"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"tajaAl~a","text_ar":"تَجَالَّ"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"taraf~aEa","text_ar":"تَرَفَّعَ"},{"kind":"text","text":".]"}],"source_refs":["S","K","Zj"]}]},"classical_definitions":null}